===Etymology===
From {{etyl|enm}} {{term|shoo|lang=enm}}, from {{etyl|ang|en}} {{term|scoh|scōh|shoe|lang=ang}}, from {{proto|Germanic|skōhaz||skōhwaz|shoe", literally "covering|lang=en}} (cf. West Frisian {{term|skoech|lang=fy}}, German {{term|Schuh|lang=de}}, Danish {{term|sko|lang=da}}), from {{proto|Indo-European|skeuk-}} (cf. Tocharian B {{term|skak|skāk|lang=txb}} ‘balcony’), from {{proto|Indo-European|title=|(s)keu-|to cover|lang=en}}. More at {{l|en|sky}}.

